'''Minister Pius Thicknesse''' was a [[Great Britain|British]] [[Wizardkind|wizard]] and a [[British Ministry of Magic|Ministry of Magic]] official in the mid to late [[1990s]]. During the [[Second Wizarding War]], he became Head of the [[Department of Magical Law Enforcement]] as well as, later in the war, the thirty-fourth [[Minister for Magic]] under [[Tom Riddle|Lord Voldemort's]] puppet [[Fall of the British Ministry of Magic|regime]] while under the [[Imperius Curse]] and thus essentially Voldemort's puppet himself. 

He replaced [[Rufus Scrimgeour]] as Minister for Magic, who had been murdered by Voldemort. Thicknesse took part in the [[Battle of Hogwarts|final conflict of the war]], where he fought alongside the [[Death Eaters]], still under the [[curse]].

He was ousted from power after Voldemort's defeat and was succeeded by [[Kingsley Shacklebolt]] in his post of Minister for Magic.

==Biography==
===Early life===
Thicknesse was born to the wizarding Thicknesse family.<ref name="blood"/> He ultimately became employed by the [[British Ministry of Magic]] at some point in his adult life.<ref name="DH1"/>

===Head of the Department of Magical Law Enforcement {{C|1996–1997}}===
{{Quote|&#8203;''[…]'' as Head of the Department of Magical Law Enforcement, Thicknesse has regular contact not only with the Minister himself, but also with the Heads of all the other Ministry departments.|[[Corban Yaxley]], concerning Thicknesse's post as Head of the [[Department of Magical Law Enforcement]]|Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows}} 
When [[Amelia Bones]], Head of the [[Department of Magical Law Enforcement]], was murdered by [[Tom Riddle|Voldemort]] in the summer of [[1996]],<ref name="HBP1">{{HBP|B|1}}</ref> Thicknesse was appointed her successor, presumably by then-[[Minister for Magic]] [[Rufus Scrimgeour]].<ref name="DH1"/>

===Under the Imperius Curse {{C|1997–1998}}===
{{Dialogue a-b-a|Lord Voldemort|Well, Yaxley? ''Will'' the Ministry have fallen by next Saturday?|Yaxley|My Lord, I have good news on that score. I have — with difficulty, and after great effort — succeeded in placing an Imperius Curse upon Pius Thicknesse.|It is a start. But Thicknesse is only one man. Scrimgeour must be surrounded by our people before I act. One failed attempt on the Minister's life will set me back a long way.|[[Tom Riddle|Lord Voldemort]] and [[Corban Yaxley]] during the [[Meeting at Malfoy Manor]]|Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows}}
In the summer of [[1997]], as part of Voldemort's plan to take over the Ministry, [[Death Eaters|Death Eater]] [[Corban Yaxley]] placed the [[Imperius Curse]] on Thicknesse. He mentioned that this was more difficult than he had expected and had to do it with "great effort" (as Thicknesse's great strength of will allowed him to resist), which made him very nearly late for an important [[Meeting at Malfoy Manor|Death Eater meeting]] at [[Malfoy Manor]]. Many of the other Death Eaters were impressed with Yaxley's work, with [[Antonin Dolohov]] clapping him on the back in congratulations, but Voldemort pointed out that Thicknesse was only one man, as well as that he needed Minister [[Rufus Scrimgeour]] surrounded by his agents before he acted.<ref name="DH1"/>

Thicknesse proved useful, however. As head of the Department of Magical Law Enforcement, he had regular contact not only with the Minister himself, but also with the Heads of all the other Ministry departments, making it easier to subjugate the others. Thicknesse proceeded to do just that, remaining undiscovered and using his position to infiltrate the senior ranks of the Ministry, slowly working together to bring Scrimgeour down.<ref name="DH1"/>

Thicknesse also aided Voldemort in trapping [[Harry Potter]] at [[4 Privet Drive]], mainly by making it an imprisonable offence to connect the house to the [[Floo Network]], to place a [[Portkey]] there, or to [[Apparition|Apparate]] in or out. Ostensibly, all of this was done for Harry's protection, to prevent Voldemort from getting in at him, but, in reality, it was to prevent Harry from getting out of the house safely; the "protection" was pointless, as the [[bond of blood charm]] on Harry (from [[Lily Potter (I)|his mother]]'s blood) already made it impossible for Voldemort to harm Harry while he's there, and simply making it illegal to magically enter or leave 4 Privet Drive wouldn't stop Voldemort anyway, but it would give the Ministry an excuse to arrest Harry should he magic himself out or if someone else magics him out. The [[Trace]] was also in effect, so, if Harry or anyone around him cast a [[spell]] to get him out of there, Thicknesse, and the Death Eaters, would know.<ref name="DH4">{{DH|B|4}}</ref>

The [[Order of the Phoenix]], as a result, believed Thicknesse had 'gone over', which made him a big problem with the plan to move Harry. They abandoned the original plan (which was for Moody to take Harry by Side-Along Apparition), because it would have both alerted the Ministry and given them a reason to arrest Harry. They were unable to wait for the Trace to break, because the bond of blood charm would break with it (both spells automatically broke when the person on whom it is placed turned seventeen), leaving the house, and Harry, pregnable. As such, Thicknesse thought he had Harry cornered.<ref name="DH4"/> Due to this, the Order had to use means of magical transport that were undetectable by the Trace: [[broomstick]]s, [[Thestral]]s and [[Sirius Black's motorbike]], setting the stage for the [[Battle of the Seven Potters|flight from Little Whinging]],<ref name="DH4"/> and the murder of [[Alastor Moody]] by Voldemort.<ref name="DH5">{{DH|B|5}}</ref>

====As Minister for Magic====
{{Quote|As your new Minister for Magic, I promise to restore this temple of tolerance to its former glory. Therefore, beginning today, each employee﻿ will submit themselves... for evaluation. But know this: you have nothing to fear if you have nothing to hide.|Pius Thicknesse addresses Ministry employees in the [[Atrium]] following the implementation of the [[Fall of the British Ministry of Magic|Death Eater regime]]|Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 1}}
[[File:Thicknesse regime.png|250px|thumb|left|Pius Thicknesse, alongside [[Dolores Umbridge]], [[Albert Runcorn]] and [[Corban Yaxley]], introduces the new regime to [[British Ministry of Magic|Ministry of Magic]] employees]]
Eventually, Thicknesse and the other subverted high-ranking Ministry officials launched a [[Fall of the British Ministry of Magic|'smooth and virtually silent' coup]] alongside the [[Death Eaters]],<ref name="DH11"/> and on [[1 August]] [[1997]], the Ministry fell.<ref name="DH8">{{DH|B|8}}</ref> The ''[[Daily Prophet]]'' was also taken over, with the official version of Scrimgeour's murder being that he resigned and that Thicknesse had replaced him. Only the Order seemed to be aware that he was under the Imperius Curse. As a result, Thicknesse was nothing but a puppet, taking care of everyday business while Voldemort, effectively the true Minister, was free to extend his power beyond the Ministry.<ref name="DH11"/>

Thicknesse, at Voldemort's direction, installed a new regime at the Ministry that was more in line with [[Death Eaters|Death Eater]] ideology.<ref name="DH11"/> His actions included having a [[Magic is Might statue|statue]] depicting a witch and wizard on top of a throne made from the bodies of crude-looking [[Non-magic people|Muggle]]s inscribed with the motto "[[Magic is Might]]" set up in the [[Atrium|Ministry Atrium]], replacing the [[Fountain of Magical Brethren]].<ref name="DH12">{{DH|B|12}}</ref> [[Corban Yaxley|Yaxley]] succeeded Thicknesse as head of the [[Department of Magical Law Enforcement]],<ref name="DH12"/> and several other Death Eaters, such as [[Travers]]<ref name="DH13"/> and [[Selwyn]],<ref name="DH21">{{DH|B|21}}</ref> were appointed to other powerful positions within the Ministry.

Meanwhile, at [[Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry|Hogwarts School]], the [[Dark Arts]] and [[Muggle Studies#1997|prejudiced depictions of Muggles]] were taught by professors [[Amycus Carrow|Amycus]] and [[Alecto Carrow]] respectively under the new [[Headteacher|Headmaster]], [[Severus Snape]].<ref name="DH12"/> Hogwarts attendance became mandatory as well as students having to prove their blood-status, with [[Muggle-born]]s removed.<ref name="DH11"/> [[Harry Potter]] was declared 'Undesirable No. 1', wanted for questioning about the death of [[Albus Dumbledore]]<ref name="DH13"/> with a ten-thousand-[[Galleon]] reward on his head<ref name="DH12"/> (which was by [[March]] [[1998]] increased to two-hundred-thousand when attempts to find him all over the country continued to fail).<ref name="DH23">{{DH|B|23}}</ref>

Using falsified research done in the [[Department of Mysteries]], the Ministry claimed that [[Muggle-born]]s 'stole' their magic from 'real' witches and wizards. As a result, the [[Muggle-Born Registration Commission]] was set up to persecute and imprison Muggle-borns,<ref name="DH11"/> with [[Dolores Umbridge]] as its head.<ref name="DH13"/> To round up any Muggle-borns or [[blood traitor]]s on the run, the [[Snatchers]] organisation was formed.<ref name="DH19">{{DH|B|19}}</ref> People with known connections to the [[Order of the Phoenix]] or sympathies for Muggles, such as [[Arthur Weasley]], were also put under surveillance.<ref name="DH13"/>

====Encountering Harry Potter====
{{Dialogue a-b-a-b-a|Thicknesse|What brings you here, Runcorn?|Harry Potter {{c|as Runcorn}}|Needed a quick word with Arthur Weasley. Someone said he was up on level one.|Ah. Has he been caught having contact with an Undesirable?|No. No, nothing like that.|Ah, well. It's only a matter of time. If you ask me, the blood traitors are as bad as the Mudbloods. Good day, Runcorn.|Thicknesse encounters whom he believes to be Albert Runcorn|Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows}}
[[File:Pius Thicknesse's sycophants.jpg|250px|thumb|right|Thicknesse and [[Albert Runcorn]] (actually [[Harry Potter]] in [[Polyjuice Potion|disguise]]) within the Ministry]]
When [[Harry Potter]], [[Hermione Granger]], and [[Ronald Weasley|Ron Weasley]] [[Infiltration of the British Ministry of Magic (1997)|infiltrated the Ministry]] in search of one of Voldemort's [[Horcrux]]es, Harry encountered Thicknesse while in the form of [[Albert Runcorn]], with whom Thicknesse seemed familiar. Thicknesse, at the time, was wearing magnificent robes of black and gold.<ref name="DH13"/>

Harry witnessed Thicknesse's altered nature while under the Imperius Curse, which showed him having a strong hatred for Muggle-borns, referring to them as '[[Mudblood]]s', as well as [[blood traitor]]s, whom he claimed to despise just as much. While Harry was searching for the Horcrux in Umbridge's office, Thicknesse arrived momentarily to jot down a note, as well as almost discovered Harry while he was under the [[Cloak of Invisibility|invisibility cloak]], though he ultimately failed to notice him.<ref name="DH13"/>

In late [[1997]], [[Xenophilius Lovegood]]'s [[Luna Lovegood|daughter]] was kidnapped in order to stop his telling the truth to the public and encouraging support of Harry Potter in his magazine, ''[[The Quibbler]]''. Hoping to get her back, he sent an owl to the Ministry when Harry, Hermione, and Ron came to see him. Thicknesse promptly dispatched Travers and Selwyn to investigate. They arrested Lovegood, but failed to capture the trio.<ref name="DH21"/>

====[[Battle of Hogwarts]]====
{{Quote|Hello, Minister! Did I mention I'm resigning?|[[Percy Weasley]] while [[duelling]] his former boss|Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows}}
[[File:Harry-potter7-Death Eaters.jpg|250px|thumb|left|Thicknesse wearing [[Death Eaters|Death Eater]] robes during the Battle of Hogwarts]]<!-- DO NOT put that Thicknesse died in the Battle of Hogwarts. That event, as depicted in the film, contradicts the novel. -->
During the Battle of Hogwarts, Thicknesse was stationed within the ranks of the [[Death Eaters]] and fought with them against the castle's defenders. He was amongst a group of masked and hooded Death Eaters who successfully penetrated Hogwarts and duelled with [[Percy Weasley]]. His hood slipped off as he tried to avoid being cursed and Percy mocked his former boss before using a [[Sea Urchin Jinx]], causing Thicknesse to sprout sea urchin-like spikes all over his body. The corridor they were in was then damaged in an explosion that killed [[Fred Weasley]].<ref name="DH31">{{DH|B|31}}</ref> Thicknesse and his comrades later retreated at Voldemort's command.<ref name="DH33">{{DH|B|33}}</ref>

When the battle later recommenced, moments prior to the [[Voldemort's Last Stand|duel that ended the War]], Thicknesse was "floored" by [[Arthur Weasley|Arthur]] and [[Percy Weasley]].<ref name="DH36">{{DH|B|36}}</ref>

===Later life {{C|1998–}}===
{{Quote|&#8203;''[…]'' the Imperiused up and down the country had come back to themselves, that Death Eaters were fleeing or else being captured, that the innocent of Azkaban were being released at that very moment, and that Kingsley Shacklebolt had been named temporary Minister for Magic.|Description of the events immediately after the end of the [[Battle of Hogwarts]]|Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows}}
It is uncertain if Thicknesse was killed during the battle or just [[Stunning Spell|stunned]]. The latter seems more likely, as [[Arthur Weasley]], like the rest of the [[Order of the Phoenix]], knew Thicknesse was under the influence of the [[Imperius Curse]].<ref name="DH4"/> After [[Tom Riddle|Voldemort]]'s death, all the people across the country who had been under the [[Imperius Curse]] came back to themselves. If he survived the battle, this would include Thicknesse. Right after the battle, [[Kingsley Shacklebolt]] was named temporary [[Minister for Magic]], which later became a permanent appointment.<ref name="DH36"/> If Thicknesse did survive the battle, it is unclear if he rejoined the Ministry or was incarcerated. The latter possibility is unlikely, as he was acting under the Imperius Curse and had no control over his actions. 

In spite of effectively having served as the 34th British [[Minister for Magic]] from [[1997]] to [[1998]], Thicknesse was omitted from most official records about the [[Fall of the British Ministry of Magic|Death Eater regime]],<ref name="PM-ministers">{{HPcom|ministers-for-magic}}</ref> as his unconsciousness eschewed any responsibility for his actions at the time.

==Physical description==
Thicknesse was described as having long black hair and a beard streaked with silver, as well as 'a great overhanging forehead' that shadowed his glinting eyes.<ref name="DH13"/> [[Harry Potter]] thought he resembled a [[crab]] looking out from beneath a rock.<ref name="DH13"/>

==Personality and traits==
It is unknown what Thicknesse was like before the [[Imperius Curse]] was placed upon him, or after it was removed when [[Tom Riddle|Voldemort]] was defeated. While under the effects of the Curse, however, his air of lofty authority mixed with his appearance made him generally intimidating and supportive of the way things were being run at the [[British Ministry of Magic|Ministry]] under himself and the [[Death Eaters]], casually espousing the view that [[blood traitor]]s were as bad as [[Mudblood]]s to [[Harry Potter]], who was [[Polyjuice Potion|disguised]] as [[Albert Runcorn]] at the time.<ref name="DH13"/>

It would be unfair to judge Thicknesse solely on his activities during his [[1997–1998 school year|tenure as Minister for Magic]], however, as he was being controlled by the Death Eater [[Corban Yaxley]] at the time and was not responsible for his actions. However, since the Death Eaters ended up resorting to the [[Imperius Curse]] to get Thicknesse in the position of [[Minister for Magic]] and his name was removed from most official records afterwards,<ref name="PM-ministers"/> it is safe to say that he was likely not a sympathiser of their ideals.

As Head of the [[Department of Magical Law Enforcement]], the largest department in the Ministry, it can be presumed that he was a fairly capable [[Wizardkind|wizard]] and law enforcement official. It is implied that he was a strong-willed individual, as he tried very hard to [[Spell resistance|resist]] the effects of the [[Imperius Curse]].<ref name="DH1"/>

